      <hedline>
        <hl1>Corrections</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Correction of April 11 Science Times article on efforts to track mountain gorillas in Rwanda and nearby areas which referred imprecisely to research by Jane Goodall on chimpanzees and Dian Fossey on mountain gorillas</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>An article in Science Times on April 11 about efforts to track mountain gorillas in Rwanda and nearby areas referred imprecisely to research by Jane Goodall on chimpanzees and Dian Fossey on mountain gorillas. Though both were pioneering researchers, they were not the first to describe the animals' lives in the wild. Earlier scholars included George Schaller and Robert M. Yerkes. This correction was delayed by efforts to check other points questioned by a reader, but those proved correct.</p>
      </block>
